    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Newel</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Venezuelan arbitration finished hearing arguments yesterday noon. Adjourned with
                    announcement by tribunal that parties may put in <pb facs="0594" n="506"
                        xml:id="pg_506"/> tabulated statements without comment or argument of the
                    awards of mixed commission at Caracas until December 15, inclusive. They are to
                    be handed to secretary-general in sufficient quantity for distribution. About
                    one hundred copies should be printed and sent immediately. Tribunal further
                    announced its decision will be rendered and communicated in due time. It is
                    understood that they will meet here, probably in February, for that purpose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Newel.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
